<subSubSection pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,726,752]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Comments</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[342,562,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Phenacoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bromi">
<emphasis box="[342,562,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Phenacoccus bromi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an unusual species of 
<taxonomicName box="[833,981,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Phenacoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[833,981,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Phenacoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that it lacks multilocular and quinquelocular pores, and has tarsal digitules that are capitate.
</paragraph>
